            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Akshayah was one of Chennai's top 3 schools in the late 2000's and early 2010's. It lost its charm and educating prowess and its downfall started after the Principal Mrs. Kumud Raj retired. The correspondent Mr. Venkatesh introduced Global Education and messed up the functioning of the institute due to his personal issues. Teachers weren't paid and in the end the school shut down post COVID. New efforts were made to reopen the premises by the Chettinad group a year or so ago. Now only memories remain of what was once a great institution and a second home for few of us who studied there from Day 1.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
