            "name": "Jeeva John"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-02-17",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Good school. Good educated people as Correspondent and Secretary . My son started his education  there  & is still there. They dont trouble parents with unwanted complaints of their wards.If the school exist I would rather happily continue his Education there at Akshayah.\nThe school campus is aesthetically designed. The school's anthem is a wonderful one that I admire a lot.\nThis school helps the students to learn & never try to thrust studies on them.Friendly teachers with good parental care are the gems in the crown of Akshayah.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Akshayah Global School - Velachery"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "A “At” T"
          },
          "datePublished": "2020-09-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I studied and am still studying here(10th grade)(matriculation board). Truly one of the best schools. I don't know about the Global one though. Great and understanding teachers who know and understand the students. Friendly non teaching staff. Vice principal Mrs Shima Newton mam is very caring and understanding and listens thoroughly to the student's problems and suggests solutions. New turf  with artificial grass has been made which prevents major injuries. Nice library with lots of books and friendly librarian. AV room with AC, giant Toshiba television and super comfy seats  for study presentation and choir class.\nGreat, big,  sports ground with snack shop and coaches for students from 6-9th who go there every Friday for football, cricket, tabletennis, badminton, tennis and basketball. Clean and new age Jaguar fitting toilets with no stench and running water with regular cleaning on 1st 2nd and 3rd floor. Sports room with tons of equipment. Bus service provided.Timings are EXTREMELY convenient (8 00-2 20) (online class 8 00- 1 15 and 15 min break between each class). They don't treat students on mark basis but treat equally.ECA activities are excellent. Overall worth the money.👍👍👌👌I request the people with negative review to reconsider and check again. Awesome place for friendship and all round development.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
